data.content:
Anh - Anh
gora
['gɔ:rə]
■ noun (fem. gori) (plural goras'gɔ:rəz or goray'gɔ:reɪ) (in the Indian subcontinent, and among British Asians) a white person.
Origin
from Hindi gorā 'fair, white'.
